<TITLE> France's Sarkozy drops legal case over SMS story </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 PARIS, March 19 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - President Nicolas Sarkozy has dropped a legal suit against a magazine that said he had sent a text message to his former wife asking her to return, the French leader's new wife said on Wednesday. Carla Bruni, who married Sarkozy last month, wrote in Le Monde newspaper that her husband had decided to withdraw the case against Le Nouvel Observateur after the journalist concerned wrote to her and apologised. "The story of the false SMS is now closed," Bruni said in a column entitled "End calumny", in which she attacked news organisations for blurring fact and fiction. "If major newspapers fail to sift out the gossip from the facts, where will we end up?" she wrote. The Nouvel Observateur article had said that a week before he married Bruni, Sarkozy sent a brief text message to former wife Cecilia Ciganer-Albeniz which said: "If you come back, I'll call everything off." The story helped further dent Sarkozy's already battered image and the president launched a criminal case against le Nouvel Observateur, accusing it of falsification and handling falsified documen
